Title : Salamon Mørkved
Text : '''Salamon Mørkved''' (27 September 1891 – 30 June 1978) was a Norwegian forester and politician for the [[Liberal Party (Norway)|Liberal Party]].

==Personal life==
He was born in [[Høylandet]] as a son of [[Lorents Mørkved]] (1844–1924) and Sofie Aavatsmark (1850–1935).<ref name=salamon>{{cite encyclopedia|year=1973|title=Mørkved, Salamon|encyclopedia=[[Hvem er hvem?]]|editor=Steenstrup, Bjørn|publisher=Aschehoug|location=Oslo|url=http://runeberg.org/hvemerhvem/1973/0402.html|page=402|language=Norwegian|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref> He was a nephew of [[Ivar Aavatsmark]] and brother-in-law of [[Albert Fredrik Eggen]].

In 1919 he married Inga Bertha Aavatsmark (1892–1967), a daughter of farmers Andreas Hammer (1849–1918) and Bereth Aavatsmark (1852–1925). They resided at [[Spillum]].<ref name=salamon/>

==Career==
Mørkved finished folk high school (1909), forester school (1911), commerce school (1912) before enrolling in higher education, graduating in forestry from the [[Norwegian College of Agriculture]] in 1917. He was hired as a forest manager in [[Namdal Aktiedampsag & Høvleri]] in 1918, then as timber director in [[Namdalsbruket]] in 1920. From 1934 he was the manager and owner of [[Spillumbruket]]. He chaired Namdal Forestry Society from 1941 to 1961 and was a board member of the [[Norwegian Forestry Society]] from 1942 to 1960.<ref name=salamon/>

While working for Namdalsbruket, Mørkved was elected to [[Namsos]] [[municipal council (Norway)|municipal council]] from 1927 to 1934. He was elected to [[Klinga (municipality)|Klinga]] [[municipal council (Norway)|municipal council]] from 1946 to 1950. He also served as public trustee here from 1948 to 1962.<ref name=salamon/>

Mørkved also chaired Klinga Sparebank from 1945 to 1962 and Den Nordenfjeldske Trelastforening. He was a board member of Namsos Sparebank from 1936 to 1963, and supervisory council member of Namdal Dampskibsselskab from 1935 to 1963 and Det norske gjensidige Skogbrandforsikringsselskap.<ref name=salamon/>

He was decorated with the [[King's Medal of Merit|King's Medal of Merit in gold]].<ref name=salamon/> He died in June 1978 and was buried in Namsos.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.disnorge.no/gravminner/index.php?language=engelsk|title=Cemeteries in Norway|publisher=DIS-Norge|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref>

